<p><b>William Somerset Maugham</b> (pronounced 'mawm'), <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_Companions_of_Honour" title="Order of the Companions of Honour">CH</a> (25 January 1874 – 16 December 1965) was an <a href="/wiki/English_language" title="English language">English</a> <a href="/wiki/Playwright" title="Playwright">playwright</a>, <a href="/wiki/Novelist" title="Novelist" class="mw-redirect">novelist</a> and <a href="/wiki/Short_story" title="Short story">short story</a> <a href="/wiki/Writer" title="Writer">writer</a>. He was one of the most popular <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">authors</a> of his era, and reputedly the highest paid of his profession during the 1930s. <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
